 compute hardware to vertically integrate into chip design and manufacturing, aiming to alleviate future chip shortages and reduce compute costs.\n\n### **Additional Subsequent AI Infrastructure Investments**\nBeyond the standard capex tables, the filing notes an additional infrastructure purchase:\n*   **Turbine Purchases:** In March 2026, SpaceX executed a purchase agreement with an unaffiliated third party to acquire additional turbines for the AI infrastructure totaling **$805 million** through 2029. (COLOSSUS II is noted as being capable of operating entirely by a self-built, behind-the-meter gigawatt-scale natural gas power plant).',
